f=Cybersecurity/warden/marketplace/vendor-ai-risk/SKILL.md · in=Evaluate third-party vendors tools across five specialized dimensions: security, privacy, AI-specific risks, contractual protections, regulatory compliance. Designed growing category vendor assessments general vendor review skills don't cover training data rights, model behavior guarantees, output ownership, AI-specific regulatory obligations. · wu=Assessing vendor, LLM API, AI-powered tool processes business data., "Is vendor safe," "what AI-specific risks," "does tool comply our policies.", Supplementary primary Anthropic vendor-review skill AI-specific dimensions. · h3:Quick Triage (5 minutes)=fast red-flag screening initial procurement filtering. Answers: "Should spend time vendor, pass now?" · h3:Deep Due Diligence (full assessment)=Comprehensive evaluation detailed risk scorecard (0-100 dimension) go/no-go recommendation. · h2:Five Assessment Dimensions=**Security** infrastructure security, certifications, data handling, access controls **Privacy** data collection practices, retention, subprocessors, user consent **AI-Specific Risks** training data provenance, model behavior guarantees, output ownership, bias fairness, explainability **Contractual Protections** indemnification, liability caps, SLA commitments, termination rights **Regulatory Compliance** GDPR, CCPA, Act readiness, sector-specific regulations · of=`## AI Vendor Assessment: [vendor name] \· Triage: [PASS / FLAG / NEEDS REVIEW] \· Deep Due Diligence: \· Security: [score/100 \· key findings] \· Privacy: [score/100 \· key findings]` · b=Use alongside primary **Anthropic vendor-review** complete vendor assessment., AI-specific findings feed warden's risk-register., Contractual findings coordinate future Legal department.